content: Hello.  I am a retired Information Technology professional.  Are there volunteer roles that would utilize my skills?  If so, how may I find out about the specific opportunities?
Hi <@1009873386190667866> I really appreciate your reaching out to share your skills. I encourage you to attend one of the vote team trainings and then volunteer to be a chat captain.
[Data Captain training](https://events.democrats.org/event/654890/)
Put him on the problem of people trying to stay on their computer to call people. They shouldn't have to disconnect and use their phones.
Thank you for the replies.  I have signed up for the VOTE Team Data Captain Training.
I was going to suggest data captain role here as well! Thanks

What about someone myself who has other type of skills? I am working two part time jobs one a library assistant and the other I work a non-profit organization that parts with the IRS for the Vita program! I have experience using social media like Facebook, twitter and I just register for Discord learning about it LinkedIn!
<@1254167148457103405>  It sounds like you might really enjoy our [Online Engagement Team training Part 1: Mapping Your Digital Communities](https://events.democrats.org/event/615101/)
Thanks <@791857656897732648>  I was hoping to do something other than banking and canvassing, too. I will join my first data captain training in 2 hours. Thanks again for the recommendation.
<@1266879741785538682> thank you Jean I will definitely registered for online engagement for part 1 and part 2
<@1266879741785538682> this will be great to learn new skills to add to my resume!
You're so welcome! Let us know if we can help you find other ways to get involved, too. You're making a difference and we really appreciate it!

<@1266879741785538682> my mistake it is 7-8 pm good!
